Well, we talked about that choice thing

00:46:48.079 --> 00:46:50.779
but there's responsibility and there's accountability.

00:46:51.920 --> 00:46:54.320
The chastening of the Lord is a real thing

00:46:54.320 --> 00:46:56.559
and if you wanna deal with the chastisement of the Lord,

00:46:56.559 --> 00:46:58.640
that's up to you, man, that's the decision that you make

00:46:58.640 --> 00:47:00.959
and the consequence that follows

00:47:00.959 --> 00:47:02.720
because whom the Lord loveth, he chasteneth,

00:47:02.720 --> 00:47:04.959
that's what the Bible says

00:47:04.959 --> 00:47:06.739
and so we find here this morning that listen,

00:47:06.739 --> 00:47:10.579
many of us have been saved, we have been made free.

00:47:10.579 --> 00:47:12.260
My question is simply this,

00:47:12.260 --> 00:47:15.440
are we living in the freedom that we have in Christ?

00:47:15.440 --> 00:47:17.399
Not the freedom to go do whatever we wanna do.

00:47:17.399 --> 00:47:20.000
Listen, I believe today that the generation in America

00:47:20.000 --> 00:47:21.799
doesn't understand freedom properly.

00:47:22.959 --> 00:47:24.799
We're talking about it nationally.

00:47:24.799 --> 00:47:29.380
I don't think they understand freedom properly, all right?

00:47:29.380 --> 00:47:32.880
But as believers, because that's the focus of the message

00:47:32.880 --> 00:47:34.799
because we're a church, I'm not a politician,

00:47:34.799 --> 00:47:35.640
I'm not trying to be out there

00:47:35.640 --> 00:47:39.200
and deal with the problems in society from that perspective

00:47:39.200 --> 00:47:44.200
but as a church, a body of believers,

00:47:44.739 --> 00:47:45.579
what am I saying?

00:47:45.579 --> 00:47:47.940
Listen, don't misunderstand your freedom.

00:47:49.179 --> 00:47:51.179
We have freedom to serve Christ.

00:47:51.179 --> 00:47:52.779
We have freedom to live for him.

00:47:52.779 --> 00:47:56.459
We have freedom to please him and what a blessing that is.

00:47:56.459 --> 00:47:57.899
Listen, I don't know if you remember

00:47:57.899 --> 00:47:59.619
what it was to be bound by sin.

00:48:00.500 --> 00:48:02.679
I don't remember if you knew what it was

00:48:02.679 --> 00:48:04.660
to be in that place as Paul talks about

00:48:04.660 --> 00:48:07.859
in the book of Romans when he was in bondage to sin.

00:48:07.859 --> 00:48:10.059
Romans chapter number six talks about it quite a bit

00:48:10.059 --> 00:48:13.079
and talking about the fact that we have been made free.

00:48:13.079 --> 00:48:15.720
He says, for sin shall not have dominion over you

00:48:15.720 --> 00:48:17.320
for you're not under the law but under grace.

00:48:17.320 --> 00:48:19.220
Listen, I'm thankful to no longer

00:48:19.220 --> 00:48:21.760
be under the dominion of sin.

00:48:23.760 --> 00:48:25.279
Those people in John chapter number eight,

00:48:25.279 --> 00:48:27.320
they heard Jesus speak.

00:48:27.320 --> 00:48:29.079
They heard him teach.

00:48:29.079 --> 00:48:32.980
And as he is teaching, he tells them,

00:48:34.400 --> 00:48:36.840
if you continue my word, then are you my disciples indeed

00:48:36.859 --> 00:48:37.900
and you shall know the truth

00:48:37.900 --> 00:48:40.340
and the truth shall make you free.

00:48:40.340 --> 00:48:42.219
And there were those that were delusional

00:48:42.219 --> 00:48:45.140
and they said, we've never been in bondage.

00:48:45.140 --> 00:48:47.380
And Jesus says, verily, verily I say unto you,

00:48:47.380 --> 00:48:51.520
whosoever committeth sin is the servant of sin.

00:48:51.520 --> 00:48:54.419
If the son therefore shall make you free,

00:48:54.419 --> 00:48:57.359
you shall be free indeed.

00:48:57.359 --> 00:48:59.820
I'm thankful for the freedom that I have as an American

00:48:59.820 --> 00:49:01.059
but more importantly than that,

00:49:01.059 --> 00:49:03.500
I'm thankful for the freedom that I have in Christ.

00:49:03.500 --> 00:49:06.219
You know what the reality is this morning?

00:49:06.219 --> 00:49:07.400
I hope this doesn't happen.

00:49:07.400 --> 00:49:09.080
I'm not trying to be prophetic.

00:49:09.080 --> 00:49:10.679
I'm just being real with you.

00:49:10.679 --> 00:49:14.080
Somebody could come and take our freedom as Americans.

00:49:15.799 --> 00:49:16.640
Right?

00:49:16.640 --> 00:49:17.460
Oh, it's never gonna happen.

00:49:17.460 --> 00:49:19.880
You better get your head out of the sand.

00:49:19.880 --> 00:49:22.179
I hope that it never happens

00:49:22.179 --> 00:49:24.619
but it is absolutely possible

00:49:24.619 --> 00:49:27.179
that our freedom as Americans could be taken away.

00:49:28.840 --> 00:49:30.320
But you know what I'm thankful for?

00:49:30.320 --> 00:49:33.979
No one can take away my freedom that I have in Christ.

00:49:33.979 --> 00:49:35.400
Nobody.

00:49:35.419 --> 00:49:36.260
Nobody.

00:49:38.140 --> 00:49:42.539
And I'm so thankful to have that freedom.

00:49:42.539 --> 00:49:45.719
Yes, I'm thankful for the freedom that I have as an American

00:49:45.719 --> 00:49:48.780
but more importantly and more precious

00:49:48.780 --> 00:49:51.900
is the freedom that I have in Christ.

00:49:51.900 --> 00:49:56.900
And we know so many people that have freedom as Americans

00:49:56.900 --> 00:49:58.500
but they're in bondage to sin.

00:49:59.500 --> 00:50:01.020
And the question is this.

00:50:01.020 --> 00:50:02.980
What do we do about it?

00:50:02.980 --> 00:50:05.820
Are we going out there preaching the gospel?

00:50:05.820 --> 00:50:07.580
Are we telling about the compassion of Christ?

00:50:07.580 --> 00:50:11.540
Are we being compassionate to tell them

00:50:11.540 --> 00:50:13.580
of the one who died for them

00:50:13.580 --> 00:50:17.220
so that they could be delivered from the bondage of sin

00:50:17.220 --> 00:50:20.860
and have freedom that we love and enjoy,

00:50:20.860 --> 00:50:23.360
the freedom that we have to serve him and to please him,

00:50:23.360 --> 00:50:26.900
to come boldly under the throne of grace?

00:50:26.900 --> 00:50:28.740
I couldn't do that when I was lost.

00:50:29.740 --> 00:50:31.180
Listen, the Old Testament folks,

00:50:31.180 --> 00:50:33.020
they couldn't do that either.

00:50:33.020 --> 00:50:34.660
Only the high priest once a year

00:50:34.660 --> 00:50:36.620
could go into the Holy of Holies.

00:50:36.620 --> 00:50:38.480
But now you and I, every day of our lives,

00:50:38.480 --> 00:50:40.300
we can come boldly under the throne of grace.

00:50:40.300 --> 00:50:41.140
Why?

00:50:41.140 --> 00:50:42.340
Because I have freedom in Christ.

00:50:42.340 --> 00:50:44.300
It's a blessing.

00:50:44.300 --> 00:50:45.860
And so this morning, do you want to be free?

00:50:45.860 --> 00:50:46.700
You say, I already am.

00:50:46.700 --> 00:50:49.900
Then live in freedom.

00:50:49.900 --> 00:50:52.180
Don't be entangled with the bondage

00:50:53.140 --> 00:50:57.020
and don't use the freedom as an occasion to the flesh.

00:50:57.020 --> 00:50:58.420
Please Christ, let's pray.

00:50:59.100 --> 00:51:00.300
Father, we love you.

00:51:00.300 --> 00:51:02.060
Thank you for loving us.

00:51:02.060 --> 00:51:03.340
Thank you for the word of God

00:51:03.340 --> 00:51:06.860
and thank you for the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:51:07.740 --> 00:51:09.740
Lord, I pray that if there's one present here

00:51:09.740 --> 00:51:11.140
or tuned in via live stream,

00:51:11.140 --> 00:51:13.980
Lord, they have a choice to make today.

00:51:13.980 --> 00:51:15.620
No one can force them.

00:51:15.620 --> 00:51:17.320
The choice is an individual choice.

00:51:17.320 --> 00:51:18.160
We've seen it.

00:51:18.160 --> 00:51:19.460
We've looked at it from the scriptures

00:51:19.460 --> 00:51:22.560
in a variety of places.

00:51:22.560 --> 00:51:25.140
And God, I pray that they'd make the right choice,

00:51:26.140 --> 00:51:29.220
that they would confess with their mouth

00:51:29.220 --> 00:51:30.340
and believe in their heart,

00:51:30.340 --> 00:51:33.140
that they would call upon the Lord Jesus Christ

00:51:33.140 --> 00:51:36.500
for salvation, recognizing that they're in bondage to sin.

00:51:37.820 --> 00:51:41.900
That law of sin and death is active and functioning.

00:51:43.100 --> 00:51:46.740
I'm thankful for the compassion of Christ.

00:51:46.740 --> 00:51:51.740
Lord, I pray that that individual would trust Christ today.

00:51:53.060 --> 00:51:55.020
Lord, I pray for every person that's been saved

00:51:55.860 --> 00:51:56.700
by the grace of God.

00:51:56.700 --> 00:51:58.820
Would you help us to live in freedom?

00:51:58.820 --> 00:52:00.660
Would you help us to please you with our lives?

00:52:00.660 --> 00:52:04.140
Thank you for the work that you do in and through us.

00:52:04.140 --> 00:52:05.460
I pray that you'd be honored and glorified.

00:52:05.460 --> 00:52:10.020
Give us a passion to reach the lost.

00:52:10.020 --> 00:52:15.020
So many that live in freedom as a citizen of this nation

00:52:15.820 --> 00:52:17.520
but are in bondage to sin.

00:52:20.420 --> 00:52:23.740
And that's got eternal consequences.

00:52:23.740 --> 00:52:26.500
Give us a burden, give us a passion.

00:52:26.500 --> 00:52:27.540
I pray that you'd have your will and way

00:52:27.540 --> 00:52:28.780
in these moments of invitation

00:52:28.780 --> 00:52:29.860
and we'll give you the glory for it.

00:52:29.860 --> 00:52:30.860
In Christ's name, we pray.

00:52:30.860 --> 00:52:32.180
Would you stand with me?

00:52:32.180 --> 00:52:33.540
Heads around, eyes are closed.

00:52:33.540 --> 00:52:35.100
Kimberly's gonna play quietly on the piano.

00:52:35.100 --> 00:52:36.940
If you're a man and not sure of heaven,

00:52:36.940 --> 00:52:38.220
the Marcus here has a Bible.

00:52:38.220 --> 00:52:39.820
We'll take a Bible and show you.

